# readToEnd()

**Instance Method**

Reads the available data synchronously up to the end of file or maximum number of bytes.

## Declaration

```swift
func readToEnd() throws -> Data?
```

## Return Value

The data available through the file handle up to the maximum size that can be represented by an [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/NSData] object or, if a communications channel, until an end-of-file indicator is returned.

## Discussion

This method invokes [doc://com.apple.foundation/documentation/Foundation/FileHandle/readData(ofLength:)] as part of its implementation.

## Reading from a File Handle Synchronously

- **availableData**: The data currently available in the receiver.
- **read(upToCount:)**: Reads data synchronously up to the specified number of bytes.
